com.jayway.restassured.matcher

Class ResponseAwareMatcher<T extends ResponseBody<T> & ResponseOptions<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jayway.restassured.matcher.ResponseAwareMatcher<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the response.

    public abstract class ResponseAwareMatcher<T extends ResponseBody<T> & ResponseOptions<T>>
extends Object
    An interface that can be implemented to create a Matcher based on the contents of a response. For example imagine that a resource "/x" returns the following JSON document: 
     {
      "userId" : "my-id",
      "href" : "http://localhost:8080/my-id"
 }
    you can then verify the href using: 
     get("/x").then().body("href", new ResponseAwareMatcher() {
                       public Matcher matcher(Response response) {
                           return equalTo("http://localhost:8080/" + response.path("userId"));
                       }
                  });
    ResponseAwareMatchers are also composable with other ResponseAwareMatchers and other Hamcrest matchers.

    Note that you can also use some of the predefined methods in RestAssuredMatchers.
